track_notes: This track is a special one! that means that is is not the regular path to the summit; just in case you need good shoes, you will enjoy the sight to the french Riviera! is a must

If you follow this track, there is a car park, do not park on the small road which is no large enought. Then clim to the summit as you fell! there is no path really; you can access via a goog path, but it is a bit longer! plenty room on summit for antenna, and the panorama is fine: sea and mountains
easy walk for this 2 summits, plenty room for car and antennas
That time it was 25cm of snow, nice place to visit
Starting from the village Courmes, there is a large car park (free) there are many path so look the map often! Plenty room on summit for antenna; in summertime get some water as there is no source.

Comming from Vence, it is a nice walk for winter.
The landscape is fine. much room on summit very large
So much way to climb this summit

Park at the Courmes parking lot (Parking du Parc Marino). The trail can be accessed by walking toward the entrance of the parking lot, and then turning right. This track shows us walking through the village instead, which is about the same distance.

The trail is very clear and easy to follow. Summit is rocky pasture with shrubs, no trees.

The 1980 plane wreck below the summit is about a 1-hour round trip from the summit. The coordinates are N 43.737525 E 7.039985 There are a couple stone huts on the way, be sure to check them out.
First Sota activation, then visit to a plane that crashed in 1980
